{"type":"text","id":"s_note","x":60,"y":288,"width":1330,"height":45,"text":"How approvals actually work: the intake STATUS (e.g. 'VP Pending') places the item on that level's agenda, built by the BOM team; the BOM member records\nApproved / Declined / Skipped in the meeting (Skipped auto-requeues to the next agenda) and updates the status, which advances the flow.\nOnly the FINAL SEVP (Vlad) approval is stamped on the intake record itself — every interim approval lives on the agendas.","originalText":"How approvals actually work: the intake STATUS (e.g. 'VP Pending') places the item on that level's agenda, built by the BOM team; the BOM member records\nApproved / Declined / Skipped in the meeting (Skipped auto-requeues to the next agenda) and updates the status, which advances the flow.\nOnly the FINAL SEVP (Vlad) approval is stamped on the intake record itself — every interim approval lives on the agendas.","fontSize":11.5,"fontFamily":3,"textAlign":"left","verticalAlign":"top","strokeColor":"#64748b","backgroundColor":"transparent","fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":1,"strokeStyle":"solid","roughness":0,"opacity":100,"angle":0,"seed":165,"version":1,"versionNonce":166,"isDeleted":false,"groupIds":[],"boundElements":null,"link":null,"locked":false,"containerId":null,"lineHeight":1.25},
